Adjust rack to top position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Shallot{1}. Halve @Red Grapes{2.25%ounce}. Strip @Thyme{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; mince leaves until you have 1 1/2 tsp (3 tsp for 4). Quarter @Lemon{1}.

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss potatoes on empty side with a drizzle of oil, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast carrots on middle rack and potatoes on top rack.)

Roast on top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @Pork Cutlets{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper.

On a #large plate{}, combine @Flour{1%tablespoon} and remaining Fry Seasoning. Add pork and press to coat all over, shaking off any excess.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.

Add coated pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. (For 4 servings, you may need to cook in batches.)

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and cover loosely with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add shallot and grapes; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, minced thyme, @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice, @Sugar{1/2%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4). Cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4). Season with salt and pepper.

Divide pork, carrots, and potatoes between plates. Spoon pan sauce over pork. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.